<TITLE> New Baitul Mokarram Khatib appointed </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 2 (bdnews24.com)  Maulana Muhammad Salahuddin has been appointed Khatib of the Baitul Mokarram national mosque, the Islamic Foundation said on Friday. Public relations officer Touhidul Islam told bdnews24.com under orders from the religious affairs ministry, the Foundation on Thursday issued the new Khatib, a person who delivers the sermon during the Friday or Eid prayers, his appointment letter. Maulana Salahuddin, former principal of Madrasa-i-Aliah, Dhaka, had been the Khatib of Gausul Azam Mosque at Mohakhali. Mufti Muhammad Nuruddin has been acting as the Khatib of Baitul Mokarram since former Khatib Maulana Ubaidul Haque's death. bd
